{"task": "crystallographic-wyckoff-position-analysis", "condition": "gold_skill", "repeat": 0, "skill_id": "benchflow-ai--pymatgen", "retrieval_correct": true, "judged_pass": false, "judged_score": 1, "judge_reason": "Agent's solution uses deprecated pymatgen modules and does not match the required analysis of Wyckoff multiplicities and symmetry as per oracle.", "solver_tokens": 2729, "judge_tokens": 904, "solution_text": "```python\nimport os\nfrom pymatgen import Structure\nfrom pymatgen.analysis.structure_analysis import SymmetryAnalyzer\n\n# Process all CIF files in current directory\nfor cif_file in os.listdir('.'):\n    if cif_file.endswith('.cif'):\n        try:\n            # Load structure from CIF\n            struct = Structure.from_file(cif_file)\n            \n            # Get space group information\n            space_group = struct.get_spacegroup()\n            print(f\"Crystal: {cif_file}\")\n            print(f\"Space Group: {space_group.symbol} ({space_group.number})\")\n            \n            # Analyze Wyckoff positions\n            analyzer = SymmetryAnalyzer(struct)\n            wyckoff = analyzer.get_wyckoff_positions()\n            \n            # Print site symmetry details\n            print(\"Wyckoff Positions:\")\n            for i, site in enumerate(struct.sites):\n                print(f\"  Site {i}: {site.specie} @ {site.frac_coords} (Wyckoff: {wyckoff[i]})\")\n            print(\"\\n\")\n            \n        except Exception as e:\n            print(f\"Error processing {cif_file}: {str(e)}\")\n```\n\n**Assumptions made:**\n1. CIF files are located in the current working directory\n2. All CIF files are valid SHELX-generated structures\n3. `pymatgen` is installed in the environment\n4. Output shows space group symbol/number and Wyckoff positions for each atomic site\n\n**Key features:**\n- Iterates through all CIF files in directory\n- Uses `SymmetryAnalyzer` to determine Wyckoff positions\n- Handles potential errors during file processing\n- Provides human-readable output of crystal symmetry analysis\n\n**Note:** This solution requires `pymatgen` to be installed (installed via `pip install pymatgen` if needed) and assumes the working directory contains CIF files. The output shows the space group symbol, number, and Wyckoff positions for each atomic site in the crystal structure."}
