{"task": "dapt-intrusion-detection", "condition": "random_wrong", "repeat": 0, "skill_id": "featbit--featbit-node-server-sdk", "retrieval_correct": false, "judged_pass": false, "judged_score": 2, "judge_reason": "Incomplete implementation: missing entropy calculation and other protocol counts required by oracle.", "solver_tokens": 4531, "judge_tokens": 990, "solution_text": "```python\nfrom scapy.all import PcapReader, IP, TCP, UDP\n\ndef count_protocols(pcap_file):\n    tcp_count = 0\n    udp_count = 0\n    with PcapReader(pcap_file) as pcap:\n        for pkt in pcap:\n            if IP in pkt and TCP in pkt:\n                tcp_count += 1\n            elif IP in pkt and UDP in pkt:\n                udp_count += 1\n    return tcp_count, udp_count\n\ntcp_count, udp_count = count_protocols('packets.pcap')\n\nwith open('/root/network_stats.csv', 'r') as f:\n    lines = f.readlines()\n\nwith open('/root/network_stats.csv', 'w') as f:\n    for line in lines:\n        if line.startswith('protocol_tcp,'):\n            parts = line.split(',')\n            parts[1] = str(tcp_count)\n            line = ','.join(parts)\n        elif line.startswith('protocol_udp,'):\n            parts = line.split(',')\n            parts[1] = str(udp_count)\n            line = ','.join(parts)\n        f.write(line)\n```"}
{"task": "dapt-intrusion-detection", "condition": "no_skill", "repeat": 1, "skill_id": null, "retrieval_correct": null, "judged_pass": false, "judged_score": 2, "judge_reason": "Solution only computes TCP/UDP counts but omits other required stats like entropy and ICMP/ARP counts needed for full credit.", "solver_tokens": 4233, "judge_tokens": 1031, "solution_text": "```python\nfrom scapy.all import rdpcap, TCP, UDP\n\n# Count TCP and UDP packets in the PCAP\ntcp_count = 0\nudp_count = 0\npcap = rdpcap('packets.pcap')\nfor packet in pcap:\n    if packet.haslayer(TCP):\n        tcp_count += 1\n    elif packet.haslayer(UDP):\n        udp_count += 1\n\n# Update the CSV file\ninput_path = '/root/network_stats.csv'\nwith open(input_path, 'r') as f:\n    lines = f.readlines()\n\nmodified_lines = []\nfor line in lines:\n    if line.startswith('#'):\n        modified_lines.append(line)\n        continue\n    parts = line.strip().split(',')\n    if len(parts) < 2:\n        modified_lines.append(line)\n        continue\n    key = parts[0].strip()\n    if key == 'protocol_tcp':\n        modified_lines.append(f\"{key},{tcp_count}\\n\")\n    elif key == 'protocol_udp':\n        modified_lines.append(f\"{key},{udp_count}\\n\")\n    else:\n        modified_lines.append(line)\n\n# Write back to the same file\nwith open(input_path, 'w') as f:\n    f.writelines(modified_lines)\n```"}
