{"task": "dialogue-parser", "condition": "retrieved_top1_full", "repeat": 0, "skill_id": "jeremylongshore--graphviz-dot-generator", "retrieval_correct": false, "judged_pass": false, "judged_score": 1, "judge_reason": "Agent's solution does not match oracle's structured node types (e.g., 'choice' nodes) and fails to handle branching logic or validate output per verifier requirements.", "solver_tokens": 3531, "judge_tokens": 1050, "solution_text": "```python\nimport json\n\ninput_path = \"/app/script.txt\"\noutput_json = \"/app/dialogue.json\"\noutput_dot = \"/app/dialogue.dot\"\n\nnodes = []\nedges = []\n\nwith open(input_path, \"r\") as f:\n    lines = f.readlines()\n\nfor i, line in enumerate(lines):\n    line = line.strip()\n    if not line:\n        continue\n    if \":\" in line:\n        speaker, text = line.split(\":\", 1)\n        speaker = speaker.strip()\n        text = text.strip()\n        node_id = f\"node{i+1}\"\n        nodes.append({\n            \"id\": node_id,\n            \"speaker\": speaker,\n            \"text\": text\n        })\n        if i > 0:\n            edges.append({\n                \"from\": f\"node{i}\",\n                \"to\": node_id\n            })\n\ngraph_data = {\n    \"nodes\": nodes,\n    \"edges\": edges\n}\n\nwith open(output_json, \"w\") as f:\n    json.dump(graph_data, f, indent=2)\n\ndot_content = \"digraph G {\\n\"\nfor node in nodes:\n    dot_content += f'  {node[\"id\"]} [label=\"{node[\"speaker\"]}: {node[\"text\"]}\"];\\n'\nfor edge in edges:\n    dot_content += f'  {edge[\"from\"]} -> {edge[\"to\"]};\\n'\ndot_content += \"}\"\n\nwith open(output_dot, \"w\") as f:\n    f.write(dot_content)\n```"}
{"task": "dialogue-parser", "condition": "hard_distractor", "repeat": 0, "skill_id": "cloudai-x--world-labs-text-prompt", "retrieval_correct": false, "judged_pass": false, "judged_score": 1, "judge_reason": "Agent's solution only parses character lines and ignores stage directions, choices, and proper node types, failing to match the oracle's comprehensive dialogue graph structure.", "solver_tokens": 6238, "judge_tokens": 1027, "solution_text": "```python\nimport re\nimport json\n\n# Read the input file\nwith open('/app/script.txt', 'r') as f:\n    lines = f.readlines()\n\n# Initialize variables\ncurrent_speaker = None\nedges = []\nnodes = set()\nprev_text = None\n\n# Regex pattern to match character lines (e.g., \"CHARACTER: dialogue\")\npattern = re.compile(r'^([A-Z]+):\\s*(.*)$')\n\nfor line in lines:\n    line = line.strip()\n    if not line:\n        continue\n    match = pattern.match(line)\n    if match:\n        speaker = match.group(1)\n        text = match.group(2).strip()\n        if current_speaker:\n            edges.append({\n                \"from\": current_speaker,\n                \"to\": speaker,\n                \"text\": prev_text\n            })\n        current_speaker = speaker\n        prev_text = text\n        nodes.add(speaker)\n    # Skip stage directions or other lines\n\n# Build JSON graph structure\nnodes_list = [{\"id\": node, \"type\": \"character\"} for node in nodes]\ngraph_data = {\n    \"nodes\": nodes_list,\n    \"edges\": edges\n}\n\n# Write JSON output\nwith open('/app/dialogue.json', 'w') as f:\n    json.dump(graph_data, f, indent=2)\n\n# Generate DOT visualization\ndot_lines = [\"digraph Dialogue {\"]\nfor node in nodes:\n    dot_lines.append(f'  \"{node}\" [label=\"{node}\"];')\nfor edge in edges:\n    dot_lines.append(f'  \"{edge[\"from\"]}\" -> \"{edge[\"to\"]}\" [label=\"{edge[\"text\"]}\"];')\ndot_lines.append(\"}\")\n\nwith open('/app/dialogue.dot', 'w') as f:\n    f.write(\"\\n\".join(dot_lines))\n```"}
